name: Kellanova
summary: Global candy and pet food giant Mars, Inc. has announced its plans to acquire the Kellanova family of snack food brands for $36 billion in 2024. The Kellanova brand portfolio includes popular snacks such as Pringles potato chips, Cheez-It crackers, and Pop-Tarts pastries. This acquisition, which is expected to close in 2024, would significantly expand Mars' presence in the global snack food market and create one of the largest snack food companies in the world. However, some consumer advocacy groups, such as Food and Water Watch, have expressed concerns that the merger could lead to higher prices and reduced product quality.

name: Leagues Cup
summary: MLS and Liga MX teams have faced off in the Leagues Cup, with Sounders FC advancing to the quarterfinals after a 4-0 win over Pumas UNAM. FC Cincinnati will host Philadelphia Union in the Round of 16. Despite the excitement, some MLS fans have boycotted the tournament, as Forbes explores the reasons behind this decision. St. Louis CITY SC's Leagues Cup run came to an end after a loss to Club América. Inter Miami CF and Columbus Crew are set to battle in the Round of 16, while LAFC will face San Jose Earthquakes. MLSsoccer.com provides guidance on how to watch Toluca FC vs. Colorado Rapids, and The Philly Soccer Page offers a match report on Philadelphia Union's 2-0 victory over CF Montreal. Inter Miami's triumph over Toronto has sparked praise for Jordi Alba's performance, as ESPN highlights his role as a "No. 10" with four assists.

name: Tina Peters
summary: Former Mesa County clerk Tina Peters' trial has drawn national attention due to its connection to Dominion Voting conspiracies. Peters, a prominent election denier, was found guilty of seven counts related to a data leak involving voting machines. Her trial has highlighted the widespread nature of election fraud conspiracies, as a friend of Peters testified about their involvement. Despite Peters' initial status as a hero to election deniers, she has been convicted and is facing charges related to election tampering. A judge has denied her acquittal, leaving the outcome of her case still uncertain. Jurors are currently deliberating in the case, while the defense has presented a defensive stance. The trial has brought to light the division within the American electorate regarding the integrity of elections.

name: Colin Kaepernick
summary: Former NFL quarterback Colin Kaepernick, who hasn't played professionally since 2016, is reportedly being considered for a coaching position with the Los Angeles Chargers. University of Michigan head coach Jim Harbaugh, who previously coached Kaepernick at the University of California, Berkeley, approached the former Super Bowl quarterback with the offer in January. Kaepernick is "considering" the offer, according to Harbaugh. While Kaepernick has not played in the NFL for several years, he has continued to train and has expressed a desire to make a comeback. Additionally, he has indicated an interest in playing flag football for Team USA at the 2028 Olympics.

Despite the challenges, athlete Noah Lyles' success in the 200-meter dash despite a COVID-19 diagnosis highlights the potential for perseverance amidst adversity. Scientific research continues to explore the long-term effects of COVID-19, while educational institutions grapple with the challenges of managing the virus' impact on learning. name: 2025 Social Security COLA increase
summary: Recent news articles suggest that the cost-of-living adjustment (COLA) for Social Security benefits is estimated to be around 2.6% in 2025. This represents a decrease from the current COLA of 8.7%, which is the highest increase in four decades. The decline is attributed to lower inflation rates, which are expected to moderate in the coming years. While the 2.6% COLA would provide a modest increase for beneficiaries, it may not fully offset the rising cost of living, especially for expenses like healthcare and housing. The final COLA determination will be announced in October 2024, based on inflation data from the third quarter of this year.

name: Starbucks CEO
summary: Starbucks has appointed Brian Niccol, the former CEO of Chipotle Mexican Grill, as its new Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. This abrupt management change comes after the departure of former CEO Laxman Narasimhan. Niccol, who successfully revived Chipotle during its period of distress, will now face the challenge of leading Starbucks through its current challenges. Investors have reacted positively to the news, as Starbucks stock has surged since the announcement. Narasimhan, who had only been in the role for three months, will receive a significant severance package upon his exit.
